originalText.text:
I've been meaning to go get a massage here and was finally able to last Labor Day weekend. I spoke to Andy on the phone who was really nice and asked him to give me a really good massage therapist.

I went on Sunday afternoon for a 90 min aromatherapy hot stone massage and Emma was my massage therapist. I was impressed by the Covid-19 protocols, taking your temperatures, masks all throughout the massage (you can remove your masks while face down), and really clean facility. While I'm used to the luxurious spas,  here in NYC I'm pretty much good with the no frills ones as long as I'm getting an excellent massage, that's what you're truly after anyway right? I was really surprised that the place actually had a wonderful spa ambiance, really clean, soft lighting, and gentle music playing. Emma was also really good and while I prefer deep tissue or hard, I always like starting with medium to see their level of strength and her medium was ale pretty strong to begin with so we stuck to that. She also checked in a few times to see if it was just right for me which is always appreciated. The hot stones were wonderful!

Honestly one of my best massage experience here in NYC. It was so good that exactly 24 hours after, on Labor Day, I decided to go for another 90 mins massage, this time with my husband for a Couples massage where we tried CBD oil. We loved it and planning to make this a biweekly date!

Thanks Andy, Emma, and Mary, for taking good care of us! Cannot wait to be back soon!

originalText.text: Thank you for an amazing massage!! My massage therapist was very accomodating when I told the front desk man that I wanted some attention to my upper back because of stress. Her pressure was on point, and she really worked my knots out. Thank goodness, because I was on the brink of a meltdown. This place is super clean, orderly, and the heated floors are a nice touch! Will be making this my massage spot in the UWS!

Not like this other places that they just want to get rid of you as soon as you are on the massage table. We are coming back more often to this place.

originalText.text:
Clean, sanitized, professional and highly recommend.

Experience:
We booked a 90 mins couple session over the weekend and received a warm welcome by the receptionist. Two female masseuse quickly guided us to our massage room. It was clean, sanitized and quiet. Throughout the session the place was quiet and everyone respected the privacy and peace. Had some difficulty conversing in English with the folks working there but overall a great experience and nice people.

Value for Money:
We got a Groupon deal on this so it was definitely worth it but the regular price is $350 which seems to be on a higher end.  So not matter how you value $ vs service, it'll definitely be a good experience and leave you relaxed at the end.

originalText.text: VERY BAD SERVICE!!! AFTER THE MASSAGE WAS OVER THE PERSON IN THE FRONT DESK I HANDED OVER A 15 percent tip. After we walked out ( andy ) the receptionist walked out and followed us and DEMANDED FOR A LARGER TIP.I HAVE NEVER EXPERIENCED THIS IN MY LIFE, EVEN AFTER GIVING A 15 percent tip HE HAD THE NERVE TO WALK OUT AND DEMAND FOR MORE TIP. I felt embarrassed and I gave him an extra 8$ for tip for 2 people which was then added to 20 percent tip EACH FOR 2 people. I received a couples 90 minute massage and I handed him 15 percent tip each for 2 people for tip and he walked out and followed me out the door demanding for a larger tip. As loyal customers of this spot, we will not be coming back here, thanks Andy. You won’t be seeing our faces anymore because of your stupidity. Demanding tip after you already received a 15 percent tip each for 2 people was very unprofessional and you just lost your business because I won’t suggest anyone to you anymore. After the massage I felt great but your unprofessional behavior for demanding a larger tip made me more tense and the massage I received went to waste. This really made me angry and I hope no one else experiences this. DO NOT GO HERE.
